The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                              Wednesday , November 11 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 10: Air India today paid a months incentives and allowances to its 30,000 employees as it prepares for a crucial meeting of its board tomorrow to decide on major cost-cutting initiatives. The board, which will meet in Chennai, is likely to take a decision on a proposal to scrap the productivity- linked incentives paid to its top managerial cadre, and adopt the financial accounts for 2008-09.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 10: Drug firm Jubilant Organosys will set up three new hospitals near Calcutta at an investment of Rs 185 crore in the next one year. The firm has a 120-bed hospital in Calcutta and is going to add two smaller ones and a large super-speciality hospital with over 450 beds, Jubilants chairman Shyam S. Bhartia said.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 10: Separate bourses could be set up for trading in shares of small and medium enterprises, while existing exchanges could also have a separate platform for SMEs, Sebi whole-time member Prashant Saran said.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 10: Deloitte today said it was bullish about the growth of its businesses in India and plans to hire over 4,000 people in the next three years.                            
	 London, Nov. 10: Vodafone has reported a 15 per cent growth in profit at 4.58 billion for the first six months of the current fiscal with India contributing significantly to revenues.
                                                                                                                           
